                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221023-70-off378 t18221023-70-crimeloc381"></join>; the prisoner came into the shop with two others, on the 9th of October, he asked for two yards of ferrett. I was in the back parlour and heard him; I was afterwards called into the shop; I asked the prisoner what he had been doing, he said nothing; I lifted up his apron. and found the shawl under it; the other ran out. I had seen it a quarter of an hour before. He begged of me to let him go.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The other two put it under my apron; I was frightened and did not like to say I had it.</p>
               <p>
